{"title":"Infarto de miocardio con arterias coronarias no obstructivas (MINOCA)-2024-1","guid":"","filepath":"/Users/criaah/Vault/📚 Resources/Mapas-Mentales/Entidades clínicas/Cardiología/Infarto de miocardio con arterias coronarias no obstructivas (MINOCA)-2024-1.smmx","root":{"id":"0","parent":"-1","text":"Infarto de miocardio con arterias\\Ncoronarias no obstructivas (MINOCA)","guid":"4tvlcYIfzggOC_auaDhNNA","children":[{"id":"1","parent":"0","text":"Perlas","guid":"","children":[{"id":"2","parent":"1","text":"¿Qué es el principal diagnóstico a\\Ntener en cuenta en MINOCA?","guid":"","children":[{"id":"3","parent":"2","text":"MINOCA es un diagnóstico de trabajo. Es importante realizar un estudio exhaustivo para definir el\\Ndiagnóstico definitivo, dado que tiene implicancias terapéuticas, pronósticas y de seguimiento. (1,2)","guid":"uqPAvhFw9e3cABCzUb-0rg","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"4","parent":"0","text":"Definición","guid":"","children":[{"id":"5","parent":"4","text":"MINOCA es un síndrome clínico heterogéneo caracterizado por infarto agudo de miocardio (IAM) sin obstrucción significativa de\\Nla arteria coronaria (estenosis > 50%) en la angiografía coronaria, que puede deberse a diversas causas subyacentes.(1,2)","guid":"gIhrGc8cvfEOg5dsEjY_8A","children":[]},{"id":"6","parent":"4","text":"También llamado: Infarto de miocardio con arterias coronarias normales (MINCA).(1)","guid":"sz05B9PlylWge6tKk6D00Q","children":[]}]},{"id":"7","parent":"0","text":"Fisiopatología","guid":"","children":[{"id":"8","parent":"7","text":"No hay una patogénesis común para la lesión miocárdica en MINOCA. El mecanismo depende de la causa subyacente.(1)","guid":"pfAOYjWXpkubkZ93tUxwCA","children":[]},{"id":"9","parent":"7","text":"En MINOCA causada por ruptura de placa, la mionecrosis puede estar mediada por\\Nuna combinación de trombosis, tromboembolismo y vasoespasmo superpuesto.(1)","guid":"LTkFPJqe5_oMXMMKVquSIQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"10","parent":"0","text":"Epidemiología","guid":"","children":[{"id":"11","parent":"10","text":"Prevalencia general de MINOCA: 6%.(1)","guid":"_utNJEVxh-6lc5KDpHRsug","children":[]},{"id":"12","parent":"10","text":"Representa 1-13% de todos los diagnósticos clínicos de IAM.(1)","guid":"EM5ohpLfeU695_Um3J_T5g","children":[]},{"id":"13","parent":"10","text":"Corresponde a 5-20% de todos los IAM tipo 1.(1)","guid":"ZL_V__PmOU8_9StdCj9TjA","children":[]},{"id":"14","parent":"10","text":"Pacientes con MINOCA tienden a ser más jóvenes que aquellos con enfermedad\\Narterial coronaria obstructiva, con solo una ligera preponderancia masculina.(1)","guid":"iN1QD21UeNsvPq0plm0Gtw","children":[]},{"id":"15","parent":"10","text":"Mayor predominio de sexo femenino y antecedentes de cáncer en\\NMINOCA en comparación con síndrome coronario agudo obstructivo.(1)","guid":"PsfE48lHM6wJgLVlp18sgQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"16","parent":"0","text":"Factores de riesgo","guid":"","children":[{"id":"17","parent":"16","text":"Causas\\Ncoronarias:(1)","guid":"v5DsAYax32ciVflOG0ILcw","children":[{"id":"18","parent":"17","text":"Ruptura o erosión de placa","guid":"JINO_TY683IA0oySvYGQXQ","children":[]},{"id":"19","parent":"17","text":"Espasmo de arteria coronaria, incluyendo espasmo microvascular","guid":"BFRpHldQzxaQTItaWTZBLw","children":[]},{"id":"20","parent":"17","text":"Disección coronaria espontánea","guid":"debWwCizqAysP18vOAPSLQ","children":[]},{"id":"21","parent":"17","text":"Disección aórtica con extensión coronaria","guid":"nxfXBRLEvHJzV9CWvuxZ9A","children":[]},{"id":"22","parent":"17","text":"Trastorno microvascular coronario (ej. síndrome X)","guid":"rPVfQmEldRfqoMfQU9T2wg","children":[]},{"id":"23","parent":"17","text":"Émbolos coronarios (ej. vegetaciones valvulares, tumores cardíacos, etc.)","guid":"bQ_vsnDILu1HWCnQVj8w6Q","children":[]},{"id":"24","parent":"17","text":"Trombosis coronaria espontánea (ej. trastornos de trombofilia)","guid":"qh3BD2cD2j_KRfhr4LQpYg","children":[]},{"id":"25","parent":"17","text":"Agentes simpaticomiméticos (ej. cocaína, metanfetaminas)","guid":"3ELxEroS3VPdvS5cu8V8hw","children":[]}]},{"id":"26","parent":"16","text":"Causas no\\Ncoronarias:(1)","guid":"k3nbE2n4pvaQI-nBi8pmZA","children":[{"id":"27","parent":"26","text":"Miocarditis","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"28","parent":"26","text":"Miocardiopatía Takotsubo","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"29","parent":"26","text":"Otras miocardiopatías","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"30","parent":"26","text":"Trauma cardíaco","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"31","parent":"26","text":"Ejercicio extenuante","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"32","parent":"26","text":"Taquiarritmias","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"33","parent":"26","text":"Cardiotoxinas (ej. quimioterapia)","guid":"qKgJXgKXPVgy91Q8hTEChA","children":[]},{"id":"34","parent":"26","text":"Derrame cerebral","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"35","parent":"26","text":"Embolia pulmonar","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"36","parent":"26","text":"Sepsis","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"37","parent":"26","text":"SDRA","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"38","parent":"26","text":"Otras causas de IAM tipo 2 (desequilibrio oferta/demanda de O2)","guid":"3F0IphYqUAScfiSmKXCTOg","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"39","parent":"0","text":"Clínica","guid":"","children":[{"id":"40","parent":"39","text":"Síntomas de síndrome\\Ncoronario agudo:(1,2)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"41","parent":"40","text":"Dolor torácico","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"42","parent":"40","text":"Angina de pecho","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"43","parent":"40","text":"Disnea","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"44","parent":"39","text":"Síntomas sugestivos de\\Nmiocardiopatía de Takotsubo:(1,2)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"45","parent":"44","text":"Similares a síndrome coronario agudo","guid":"khWhZlkYpAARq6H95CqqSg","children":[]},{"id":"46","parent":"44","text":"Insuficiencia cardíaca aguda reversible","guid":"ILl6BMF1hZrICguafiKm1A","children":[]},{"id":"47","parent":"44","text":"Desencadenante de estrés (emocional, físico, quirúrgico)","guid":"Kfat5Vo-9sLsUvD83584Bw","children":[]}]},{"id":"48","parent":"39","text":"Síntomas sugestivos de\\Ntromboembolismo cardíaco:(1)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"49","parent":"48","text":"Similares a síndrome coronario agudo","guid":"shY4QCbUj4KX_foX_Y0n_g","children":[]},{"id":"50","parent":"48","text":"Fiebre","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"51","parent":"48","text":"Signos de tromboembolismo sistémico","guid":"JB--2rE4ZS35YgooLSnJeg","children":[]},{"id":"52","parent":"48","text":"Comorbilidades de riesgo trombótico","guid":"B3jwzKWH9pd0XogwQF1LVw","children":[]}]},{"id":"53","parent":"39","text":"Preguntar por:(1)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"54","parent":"53","text":"Inicio, ocurrencia habitual y recurrencia de síntomas","guid":"OmAYEhm8mmB0N8reqmCQwA","children":[]},{"id":"55","parent":"53","text":"Síntomas desencadenados por estrés (sugiere Takotsubo)","guid":"cGX5QI_PVTAWNrpZEO518Q","children":[]},{"id":"56","parent":"53","text":"Angina en reposo o nocturna recurrente que responde a nitratos (sugiere espasmo coronario)","guid":"rKQP1meCq2XvsHKFef3ekg","children":[]},{"id":"57","parent":"53","text":"Trauma cardíaco reciente","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"58","parent":"53","text":"Uso de cardiotoxinas (ej. quimioterapia)","guid":"ysabQasTYIKrk4Fe6SGCWg","children":[]},{"id":"59","parent":"53","text":"Antecedentes de trombofilias hereditarias/adquiridas","guid":"pV--UKP41DbCy5hoEHF2bw","children":[]},{"id":"60","parent":"53","text":"Historia familiar de trastornos trombofílicos","guid":"8qNdtzt2jG7tqije1VG1BA","children":[]},{"id":"61","parent":"53","text":"Uso de simpaticomiméticos","guid":"mfetN_Zoqd-WMmX4f3nP_A","children":[]}]},{"id":"62","parent":"39","text":"Al examen físico, buscar signos de\\Ntromboembolismo sistémico:(1)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"63","parent":"62","text":"Fiebre","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"64","parent":"62","text":"Sensibilidad pantorrillas","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"65","parent":"0","text":"Estudio","guid":"6GZKJ_88vsgXHXn_k6gmcQ","children":[{"id":"66","parent":"65","text":"Después del diagnóstico de MINOCA con evaluación inicial y angiografía\\Ncoronaria, las pruebas se enfocan en identificar la causa subyacente.(1,2)","guid":"UMrzMq_71T4sAgzbYyXQig","children":[]},{"id":"67","parent":"65","text":"Análisis de sangre:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"68","parent":"67","text":"Hemograma, PCR, saturación O2 (para evaluar causas de IAM tipo 2)","guid":"FhJ59ZpW_Ni5iLRdmT1MoQ","children":[]},{"id":"69","parent":"67","text":"Dímero D (para descartar EP)","guid":"Dml5FYFnMY4rTNGBq3T_9Q","children":[]},{"id":"70","parent":"67","text":"Estudio de trombofilia","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"71","parent":"67","text":"BNP","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"72","parent":"65","text":"Pruebas no invasivas:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"73","parent":"72","text":"Ecocardiografía (evalúa motilidad parietal, puede identificar Takotsubo y otras miocardiopatías)","guid":"NupUtZy2I0n_r_qgXPkyNg","children":[]},{"id":"74","parent":"72","text":"RMC (puede detectar miocarditis o IAM)","guid":"4r9sg6AGHBQyEPaIy2CHNw","children":[]}]},{"id":"75","parent":"65","text":"Pruebas invasivas:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"76","parent":"75","text":"Revisar angiografía coronaria en búsqueda de hallazgos perdidos (disección, embolia, ruptura placa)","guid":"eRJmsqUyVGC-XC4kV_BtFA","children":[]},{"id":"77","parent":"75","text":"Test con nitratos intracoronarios (si se sospecha espasmo coronario)","guid":"IKv7lblgaxMLpI3AZT1rjA","children":[]},{"id":"78","parent":"75","text":"Ventriculografía izquierda (complementa eco en evaluación de motilidad parietal)","guid":"sn6H8PAYDQzqx9S-SFPoSQ","children":[]},{"id":"79","parent":"75","text":"Imágenes intracoronarias (IVUS, OCT) para identificar ruptura placa, erosión o disección","guid":"s_8-C4iOzhZLYHa9Z3TAKg","children":[]},{"id":"80","parent":"75","text":"Guía de presión/Doppler (identifica disfunción microvascular)","guid":"0l3H7ts3J7tJxYCiXz_EgQ","children":[]},{"id":"81","parent":"75","text":"Tests provocativos (si se sospecha espasmo coronario, idealmente no en fase aguda de IAM)","guid":"jfHNG1Lm9c24bD-gTW4FdQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"82","parent":"65","text":"Si los estudios previos no identifican causa, considerar ETE para detectar cardioembolismo.(2)","guid":"M63taZYwh6cWUhFtH9eXow","children":[]}]},{"id":"83","parent":"0","text":"Diagnóstico","guid":"","children":[{"id":"84","parent":"83","text":"Según la Sociedad Europea de Cardiología, el\\Ndiagnóstico de MINOCA requiere:(2)","guid":"BAfTO2YcS4zusZii59apIg","children":[{"id":"85","parent":"84","text":"1) Criterios de IAM","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"86","parent":"84","text":"2) Arterias coronarias no obstructivas en angiografía","guid":"Eu3NR8ZWVj3PtQ28IIdiMA","children":[]},{"id":"87","parent":"84","text":"3) Ausencia de causa clínicamente aparente para presentación aguda","guid":"ddoipuFqr0Qfhtvaz34P8A","children":[]}]},{"id":"88","parent":"83","text":"Criterios de IAM:(2)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"89","parent":"88","text":"Biomarcador cardíaco positivo (troponina) con aumento y/o caída en valores seriados","guid":"0-_fD3vKJHlbZ7Sthus7Zw","children":[]},{"id":"90","parent":"88","text":"Evidencia clínica\\Ncorroborativa:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"91","parent":"90","text":"Síntomas de isquemia","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"92","parent":"90","text":"Cambios ECG agudos","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"93","parent":"90","text":"Desarrollo de ondas Q patológicas","guid":"0Q5bsnS6Dl9fLDwh-Wzb8g","children":[]},{"id":"94","parent":"90","text":"Evidencia imagenológica de pérdida de miocardio viable o alteración de motilidad parietal","guid":"pvP5VGyTGnDWrvlgj0bLmA","children":[]},{"id":"95","parent":"90","text":"Trombo intracoronario en angiografía o autopsia","guid":"VTKBqFNIj9WMryRsS4gtYA","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"96","parent":"83","text":"Arterias coronarias no obstructivas: ausencia de estenosis >50% en cualquier arteria relacionada al infarto.(2)","guid":"das9x0EhsrNW1_se0ZDr8Q","children":[]},{"id":"97","parent":"83","text":"No hay causa clínicamente llamativa para presentación aguda evidente al momento de\\Nangiografía. Se requiere más evaluación para definir causa de MINOCA.(2)","guid":"yOHV11X_DtnYEbCb1GXJRA","children":[]}]},{"id":"98","parent":"0","text":"Diagnósticos\\Ndiferenciales","guid":"","children":[{"id":"99","parent":"98","text":"Según presentación\\Nsindromática:(1)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"100","parent":"99","text":"Dolor torácico","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"101","parent":"99","text":"Síndrome coronario agudo","guid":"ZnPJMVnf9heu5uky0BFsKA","children":[]},{"id":"102","parent":"99","text":"Insuficiencia cardíaca aguda","guid":"VLUlm2Vt-1Tj9zTiFJTqgQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"103","parent":"98","text":"Principales diagnósticos\\Ndiferenciales:(1)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"104","parent":"103","text":"Miocarditis","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"105","parent":"103","text":"Miocardiopatía Takotsubo","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"106","parent":"103","text":"Otras miocardiopatías","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"107","parent":"103","text":"Espasmo coronario","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"108","parent":"103","text":"Disección coronaria espontánea","guid":"I1DSYSVGv-mdcAZBz1B0sA","children":[]},{"id":"109","parent":"103","text":"Tromboembolismo coronario","guid":"BKSmwMKsnD2DugbsqdsBIQ","children":[]},{"id":"110","parent":"103","text":"Disfunción microvascular coronaria","guid":"Ykc1itOXHFyYh-718AFeGQ","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"111","parent":"0","text":"Tratamiento","guid":"","children":[{"id":"112","parent":"111","text":"No hay tratamiento estándar. Se dirige a la causa subyacente.(1,2)","guid":"PCYe2sqzqI9CHUQkf1JGvQ","children":[]},{"id":"113","parent":"111","text":"Espasmo coronario: bloqueadores de canales de calcio, nitratos, cese tabaco, evitar desencadenantes.(1)","guid":"Ndbt2pgq64_0y5paB8rqJg","children":[]},{"id":"114","parent":"111","text":"Ruptura de placa confirmada o sospechada: terapia antiplaquetaria dual por 1 año, luego monoterapia de por vida.(1)","guid":"0DvT2SPpztqxygluwKe9Zg","children":[]},{"id":"115","parent":"111","text":"Disección coronaria\\Nespontánea:(1)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"116","parent":"115","text":"No se recomienda estatinas.","guid":"6lUdwmLy3_wuhFOYAQiYzw","children":[]},{"id":"117","parent":"115","text":"Se puede preferir manejo conservador (intervención puede propagar la disección).","guid":"erv7O_h-4r5fEjkwg5eB2g","children":[]}]},{"id":"118","parent":"111","text":"Embolia cardíaca: anticoagulación.(1)","guid":"dCHAmU-ppjNZ5rueMa2UOQ","children":[]},{"id":"119","parent":"111","text":"Si etiología desconocida después de evaluación\\Nexhaustiva, tratamiento empírico:(1,2)","guid":"e-X6lPWdQSTooZFgnYlhoQ","children":[{"id":"120","parent":"119","text":"Terapia antiplaquetaria dual","guid":"2nYw2lwoCr7atbJZuv-EDw","children":[]},{"id":"121","parent":"119","text":"Estatinas","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"122","parent":"119","text":"Bloqueadores de canales de calcio si se sospecha vasoespasmo","guid":"XkQa9ZZo_A30eRuidQHgUA","children":[]},{"id":"123","parent":"119","text":"Rehabilitación cardiovascular (si insuficiencia cardíaca o múltiples factores de riesgo CV)","guid":"CwFmIbFhZLdB-6uqeCBH0Q","children":[]},{"id":"124","parent":"119","text":"Estatinas e inhibidores de RAAS podrían reducir eventos cardíacos adversos.(2)","guid":"s_BYhLeP8OEFDENGMlHoyA","children":[]},{"id":"125","parent":"119","text":"Clopidogrel y ticagrelor tendrían riesgo similar de MACE y sangrado en pacientes con MINOCA en DAPT.(2)","guid":"zfZ41rOM1SruwRguAOzBLA","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"126","parent":"0","text":"Seguimiento y\\Npronóstico","guid":"","children":[{"id":"127","parent":"126","text":"Pronóstico depende de causa subyacente de MINOCA.(1)","guid":"QPe1QCnPpNlmQmNdow6_WQ","children":[]},{"id":"128","parent":"126","text":"Riesgo de IAM recurrente o muerte ~2% a 12 meses.(1)","guid":"xtcqhzC4GKlEKKWz-9NCZQ","children":[]},{"id":"129","parent":"126","text":"Mortalidad intrahospitalaria 0. 9% y a 1 año 4.7%.(2)","guid":"jsWicLiKFjBE4gGhCdcrQQ","children":[]},{"id":"130","parent":"126","text":"Elevación de ST y mayor extensión de LGE en RMC se asocian a mayor riesgo de arritmia ventricular intrahospitalaria.(2)","guid":"vf7UC99E63sAmrtyd5CSRQ","children":[]},{"id":"131","parent":"126","text":"Enfermedad vascular no coronaria se asocia a mayor riesgo de eventos adversos a ~2 años en pacientes con MINOCA sin elevación de ST.(2)","guid":"wQ4FpEk2TasCxsAjNogSVA","children":[]}]}]},"node_count":131,"relations":[],"cross_references":[],"specialty":"Cardiología","folder":"Entidades clínicas/Cardiología","filename":"Infarto de miocardio con arterias coronarias no obstructivas (MINOCA)-2024-1","id":"map_295","resolved_references":[]}